cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is about pixel-level semantic segmentation, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new method for learning the segmentation results using residual blocks, which involves training the network in a level-wise manner. This suggests that the paper could also be relevant to the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on two datasets, which could also make it relevant to the category of multimedia (cs.MM).
